22/09/2004
ZAGREB, Croatia -- A delegation of the Council of Europe's European Commission Against Racism and Intolerance (ECRI) visited parliament Tuesday (21 September) and met with deputies. 
The talks were part of the team's work on a report about racism and intolerance. 
This is the third visit by ECRI representatives to Croatia.
In other news, Croatia and Germany signed a joint declaration Tuesday, stating their readiness to co-operate in the rebuilding of Afghanistan. 
The reconstruction team operates as part of the NATO-led International Security Assistance Force in Afghanistan. 
(HINA, HRT - 21/09/04)
